Compute correlation

airquality |&gt; 
    select(Ozone, Temp) |&gt;
    correlate()

# A tibble: 2 × 3
  term   Ozone   Temp
  &lt;chr&gt;  &lt;dbl&gt;  &lt;dbl&gt;
1 Ozone NA      0.698
2 Temp   0.698 NA    



Note that the diagonal values are printed as NA, but the correlation between a variable and itself is simply 1.

To just extract the single correlation value:

airquality |&gt; 
    select(Ozone, Temp) |&gt;
    correlate() |&gt; 
    filter(term == "Ozone") |&gt;
    pull(Temp)

[1] 0.6983603

